ipsecTunMonModule.name: ipsecTunMonModule
ipsecTunMonModule.contactinfo: Tim Jenkins Catena Networks 307 Legget Drive Kanata, ON Canada K2K 3C8 +1 (613) 599-6430 tjenkins@catena.com
ipsecTunMonModule.description: The MIB module to describe logical IPsec channel and tunnel objects, and entity level objects and events associated with these objects.

IpsecChanOrTunType.name: IpsecChanOrTunType
IpsecChanOrTunType.description: A value indicating an implementation specific type for channels and tunnels. The values below are defined as examples only, and are not intended to imply any specific support or capability.

ipsecTunnelMonitorMIB.name: ipsecTunnelMonitorMIB
ipsecTunnelMonitorMIB.description: This is the base object identifier for all branches.

channelObjects.name: channelObjects
channelObjects.description: This is the base object identifier for all channel related objects.

tunnelObjects.name: tunnelObjects
tunnelObjects.description: This is the base object identifier for all tunnel related objects.

channelTables.name: channelTables
channelTables.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are tables for channels.

channelStats.name: channelStats
channelStats.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are global (non-error) counters for channels.

channelErrors.name: channelErrors
channelErrors.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are global error counters for channels.

channelTraps.name: channelTraps
channelTraps.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are traps for channels.

channelTrapObjects.name: channelTrapObjects
channelTrapObjects.description: This is the base object identifier for objects which are used as part of traps for channels.

channelTrapControl.name: channelTrapControl
channelTrapControl.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are trap controls for channel traps.

channelGroups.name: channelGroups
channelGroups.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which describe the groups in the channel part of this MIB.

channelConformance.name: channelConformance
channelConformance.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which describe the conformance in the channel part of this MIB.

tunnelTables.name: tunnelTables
tunnelTables.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are tables for tunnels.

tunnelStats.name: tunnelStats
tunnelStats.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are global (non-error) counters for tunnels.

tunnelErrors.name: tunnelErrors
tunnelErrors.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are global error counters for tunnels.

tunnelTraps.name: tunnelTraps
tunnelTraps.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are traps for tunnels.

tunnelTrapObjects.name: tunnelTrapObjects
tunnelTrapObjects.description: This is the base object identifier for objects which are used as part of traps for tunnels.

tunnelTrapControl.name: tunnelTrapControl
tunnelTrapControl.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which are trap controls for tunnel traps.

tunnelGroups.name: tunnelGroups
tunnelGroups.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which describe the groups in the tunnel part of this MIB.

tunnelConformance.name: tunnelConformance
tunnelConformance.description: This is the base object identifier for all objects which describe the conformance in the tunnel part of this MIB.

currentChannels.name: currentChannels
currentChannels.description: The total number of channels currently in existence in the entity. This is the same as the number of rows in the channel table, whether there are IKE SAs for each row or not.

totalChannels.name: totalChannels
totalChannels.description: The total number of channels created by the entity since system boot. Channel creation is defined as the addition of a row to the channel table, whether an IKE SA was created at the same time or not.

deletedChannels.name: deletedChannels
deletedChannels.description: The total number of channels deleted by the entity. Channel deletion is defined as the removal of a row from the channel table, independent of the existence of the IKE SAs that may have supported it. Note that the sum of 'currentChannels' and 'deletedChannels' is equal to 'totalChannels'.

currentTunnels.name: currentTunnels
currentTunnels.description: The total number of tunnels currently in existence in the entity. This is the same as the number of rows in the tunnel table, whether there are IPsec SA suites for each row or not.

totalTunnels.name: totalTunnels
totalTunnels.description: The total number of tunnels created by the entity since system boot. Tunnel creation is defined as the addition of a row to the tunnel table, whether an IPsec SA was created at the same time or not.

deletedTunnels.name: deletedTunnels
deletedTunnels.description: The total number of tunnels deleted by the entity. Tunnel deletion is defined as the removal of a row from the tunnel table, independent of the existence of the phase 2 SA suites that may have supported it. Note that the sum of 'currentTunnels' and 'deletedTunnels' should is to 'totalTunnels'.

ipsecChannelTable.name: ipsecChannelTable
ipsecChannelTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on control channels. The number of rows in this table is, at a minimum, the same as the number of IKE SAs that have the same phase 1 ID pairs. Additional rows for channels without active phase 1 SAs may also appear in the table. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

ipsecChannelEntry.name: ipsecChannelEntry
ipsecChannelEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular control channel. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

ipsecChannelType.name: ipsecChannelType
ipsecChannelType.description: The type of control channel represented by this row. This is an implementation dependent value, used to assist in controlling how channels are sorted.

ipsecChannelLocalEndpoint.name: ipsecChannelLocalEndpoint
ipsecChannelLocalEndpoint.description: The index value of the row of the IKE Monitoring MIB's endpoint table corresponding to the local endpoint.

ipsecChannelRemoteEndpoint.name: ipsecChannelRemoteEndpoint
ipsecChannelRemoteEndpoint.description: The index value of the row of the IKE Monitoring MIB's endpoint table corresponding to the remote endpoint.

ipsecChannelCurrentSAs.name: ipsecChannelCurrentSAs
ipsecChannelCurrentSAs.description: The number of IKE SAs that are currently active that make up this channel. This value may be 0 if the channel has not yet been set up, or the implementation does not require the existence of IKE SAs for the channel to exist, or if the channel is considered a permanent entry in the table by the implementation. This value should not include SA establishment attempts in progress.

ipsecChannelTotalSAs.name: ipsecChannelTotalSAs
ipsecChannelTotalSAs.description: The total number of IKE SAs that are part of this channel that have been created in the entity since boot time. This value should not include failed SA establishment attempts.

ipsecChannelDeletedSAs.name: ipsecChannelDeletedSAs
ipsecChannelDeletedSAs.description: The total number of IKE SAs that are part of this channel that have been deleted in the entity since boot time. The sum of 'ipsecChannelCurrentSAs' and this value should equal ipsecChannelTotalSAs.

ipsecChannelTimeUpSeconds.name: ipsecChannelTimeUpSeconds
ipsecChannelTimeUpSeconds.description: The total number of seconds since there has been at least one valid IKE SA supporting the channel. In other words, the number of seconds since the value of 'ipsecChannelCurrentSAs' changed from 0 to any other value.

ipsecChannelTimeDownSeconds.name: ipsecChannelTimeDownSeconds
ipsecChannelTimeDownSeconds.description: The total number of seconds since the last valid IKE SA supporting the channel was deleted. In other words, the number of seconds since the value of 'ipsecChannelCurrentSAs' changed to 0 from any other value.

ipsecChannelInboundOctets.name: ipsecChannelInboundOctets
ipsecChannelInboundOctets.description: The amount of traffic measured in bytes received by the channel. This is the sum of 'saInOctets' from the 'saEntry' of each IKE SA in 'saTable' that is part of this channel.

ipsecChannelOutboundOctets.name: ipsecChannelOutboundOctets
ipsecChannelOutboundOctets.description: The amount of traffic measured in bytes sent by the channel. This is the sum of 'saOutOctets' from the 'saEntry' of each IKE SA in 'saTable' that is part of this channel.

ipsecChannelInboundPackets.name: ipsecChannelInboundPackets
ipsecChannelInboundPackets.description: The total number of packets received by the channel. This is the sum of 'saInPackets' from the 'saEntry' of each IKE SA in 'saTable' that is part of this channel.

ipsecChannelOutboundPackets.name: ipsecChannelOutboundPackets
ipsecChannelOutboundPackets.description: The total number of packets sent by the channel. This is the sum of 'saOutPackets' from the 'saEntry' of each IKE SA in 'saTable' that is part of this channel.

ipsecChannelReceiveErrors.name: ipsecChannelReceiveErrors
ipsecChannelReceiveErrors.description: The total number of receive errors incurred in the channel. This is the sum of all receive errors from the 'saEntry' of each IKE SA in 'saTable' that is part of this channel.

ipsecChannelSendErrors.name: ipsecChannelSendErrors
ipsecChannelSendErrors.description: The total number of send errors incurred in the channel. This is the sum of all send errors from the 'saEntry' of each IKE SA in 'saTable' that is part of this channel.

ipsecChannelCurrentTunnels.name: ipsecChannelCurrentTunnels
ipsecChannelCurrentTunnels.description: The number of IPsec tunnels that are currently active that were created by this channel. This value should not include tunnel establishment attempts that are in progress.

ipsecChannelTotalTunnels.name: ipsecChannelTotalTunnels
ipsecChannelTotalTunnels.description: The total number of IPsec tunnels that have been created in the entity by this channel since boot time. This value should not include failed tunnel establishment attempts.

ipsecChannelDeletedTunnels.name: ipsecChannelDeletedTunnels
ipsecChannelDeletedTunnels.description: The total number of IPsec tunnels that have been deleted by this channel in the entity since boot time. The sum of 'ipsecChannelCurrentTunnels' and this value should equal 'ipsecChannelTotalTunnels'.

ipsecChannelTunnelInboundOctets.name: ipsecChannelTunnelInboundOctets
ipsecChannelTunnelInboundOctets.description: The amount of traffic measured in bytes received by all tunnels created by the channel.

ipsecChannelTunnelOutboundOctets.name: ipsecChannelTunnelOutboundOctets
ipsecChannelTunnelOutboundOctets.description: The amount of traffic measured in bytes sent by all tunnels created by the channel.

ipsecChannelTunnelInboundPackets.name: ipsecChannelTunnelInboundPackets
ipsecChannelTunnelInboundPackets.description: The total number of packets received by all tunnels created by the channel.

ipsecChannelTunnelOutboundPackets.name: ipsecChannelTunnelOutboundPackets
ipsecChannelTunnelOutboundPackets.description: The total number of packets sent by all tunnels created by the channel.

ipsecChannelTunnelReceiveErrors.name: ipsecChannelTunnelReceiveErrors
ipsecChannelTunnelReceiveErrors.description: The total number of receive errors incurred in all tunnels created by the channel.

ipsecChannelTunnelSendErrors.name: ipsecChannelTunnelSendErrors
ipsecChannelTunnelSendErrors.description: The total number of send errors incurred in all tunnels created the channel.

ipsecChannelSaTable.name: ipsecChannelSaTable
ipsecChannelSaTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on which IKE SAs are used in channels. The number of rows is the same as the number of IKE SAs in the entity. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

ipsecChannelSaEntry.name: ipsecChannelSaEntry
ipsecChannelSaEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the identifiers of a specific IKE SA. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

ipsecChannelSaIndex.name: ipsecChannelSaIndex
ipsecChannelSaIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each IKE SA in the channel. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1.

ipsecChannelSaLocalIpAddrType.name: ipsecChannelSaLocalIpAddrType
ipsecChannelSaLocalIpAddrType.description: The type of the local address used to negotiate the IKE SA in the channel. (The value of 'saIkeLocalIpAddressType' from 'ikeMonModule' for this row.)

ipsecChannelSaLocalIpAddress.name: ipsecChannelSaLocalIpAddress
ipsecChannelSaLocalIpAddress.description: The local address used to negotiate the IKE SA in the channel. (The value of 'saIkeLocalIpAddress' from 'ikeMonModule' for this row.)

ipsecChannelSaRemoteIpAddrType.name: ipsecChannelSaRemoteIpAddrType
ipsecChannelSaRemoteIpAddrType.description: The type of the remote address used to negotiate the IKE SA in the channel. (The value of 'saIkeRemoteIpAddressType' from 'ikeMonModule' for this row.)

ipsecChannelSaRemoteIpAddress.name: ipsecChannelSaRemoteIpAddress
ipsecChannelSaRemoteIpAddress.description: The remote address used to negotiate the IKE SA in the channel. (The value of 'saIkeRemoteIpAddress' from 'ikeMonModule' for this row.)

ipsecChannelSaInitiatorCookie.name: ipsecChannelSaInitiatorCookie
ipsecChannelSaInitiatorCookie.description: The value of the cookie used by the initiator for the IKE SA in the channel. (The value of 'saIkeInitiatorCookie' from 'ikeMonModule' for this row.)

ipsecChannelSaResponderCookie.name: ipsecChannelSaResponderCookie
ipsecChannelSaResponderCookie.description: The value of the cookie used by the responder for the IKE SA in the channel. (The value of 'saIkeResponderCookie' from 'ikeMonModule' for this row.)

ipsecChanAggTable.name: ipsecChanAggTable
ipsecChanAggTable.description: The optional (conceptual) table containing information on aggregate statistics for the channel types. The number of rows is the same as the number of channel types supported by the entity. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

ipsecChanAggEntry.name: ipsecChanAggEntry
ipsecChanAggEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the aggregate statistics for a specific channel type. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

ipsecChanAggType.name: ipsecChanAggType
ipsecChanAggType.description: The type of control channel for which this row aggregrates statistics.

ipsecChanAggCurrentChannels.name: ipsecChanAggCurrentChannels
ipsecChanAggCurrentChannels.description: The number of channels that are currently active that are of the specified type. This value should not include channel establishment attempts in progress.

ipsecChanAggTotalChannels.name: ipsecChanAggTotalChannels
ipsecChanAggTotalChannels.description: The total number of channels of this type that have been created in the entity since boot time. This value should not include failed channel establishment attempts.

ipsecChanAggDeletedChannels.name: ipsecChanAggDeletedChannels
ipsecChanAggDeletedChannels.description: The total number of channels of this type that have been deleted in the entity since boot time. The sum of 'ipsecChanAggCurrentChannels' and this value should equal 'ipsecChanAggTotalChannels'.

ipsecChanAggInboundOctets.name: ipsecChanAggInboundOctets
ipsecChanAggInboundOctets.description: The total amount of traffic measured in bytes received by all channels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecChannelInboundOctets' from the 'ipsecChannelEntry' of each channel in 'ipsecChannelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecChanAggOutboundOctets.name: ipsecChanAggOutboundOctets
ipsecChanAggOutboundOctets.description: The total amount of traffic measured in bytes sent by all channels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecChannelOutboundOctets' from the 'ipsecChannelEntry' of each channel in 'ipsecChannelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecChanAggInboundPackets.name: ipsecChanAggInboundPackets
ipsecChanAggInboundPackets.description: The total number of packets received by all channels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecChannelInboundPackets' from the 'ipsecChannelEntry' of each channel in 'ipsecChannelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecChanAggOutboundPackets.name: ipsecChanAggOutboundPackets
ipsecChanAggOutboundPackets.description: The total number of packets sent by all channels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecChannelOutboundPackets' from the 'ipsecChannelEntry' of each channel in 'ipsecChannelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecChanAggReceiveErrors.name: ipsecChanAggReceiveErrors
ipsecChanAggReceiveErrors.description: The total number of receive errors incurred by all channels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecChannelReceiveErrors' from the 'ipsecChannelEntry' of each channel in 'ipsecChannelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecChanAggSendErrors.name: ipsecChanAggSendErrors
ipsecChanAggSendErrors.description: The total number of send errors incurred by all channels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecChannelSendErrors' from the 'ipsecChannelEntry' of each channel in 'ipsecChannelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecChanAggCurrentTunnels.name: ipsecChanAggCurrentTunnels
ipsecChanAggCurrentTunnels.description: The current number of active IPsec tunnels that have been created by all channels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecChannelCurrentTunnels' from the 'ipsecChannelEntry' of each channel in 'ipsecChannelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecChanAggTotalTunnels.name: ipsecChanAggTotalTunnels
ipsecChanAggTotalTunnels.description: The total number of IPsec tunnels that have been created by all channels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecChannelTotalTunnels' from the 'ipsecChannelEntry' of each channel in 'ipsecChannelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecChanAggDeletedTunnels.name: ipsecChanAggDeletedTunnels
ipsecChanAggDeletedTunnels.description: The total number of IPsec tunnels that have been deleted by all channels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecChannelDeletedTunnels' from the 'ipsecChannelEntry' of each channel in 'ipsecChannelTable' that is of this type. The sum of 'ipsecChanAggCurrentTunnels' and this value should equal 'ipsecChanAggTotalTunnels'.

ipsecChanAggTnlInboundOctets.name: ipsecChanAggTnlInboundOctets
ipsecChanAggTnlInboundOctets.description: The amount of traffic measured in bytes received by all tunnels created by all channels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecChannelTunnelInboundOctets' from the 'ipsecChannelEntry' of each channel in 'ipsecChannelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecChanAggTnlOutboundOctets.name: ipsecChanAggTnlOutboundOctets
ipsecChanAggTnlOutboundOctets.description: The amount of traffic measured in bytes sent by all tunnels created by all channels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecChannelTunnelOutboundOctets' from the 'ipsecChannelEntry' of each channel in 'ipsecChannelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecChanAggTnlInboundPackets.name: ipsecChanAggTnlInboundPackets
ipsecChanAggTnlInboundPackets.description: The total number of packets received by all tunnels created by all channels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecChannelTunnelInboundPackets' from the 'ipsecChannelEntry' of each channel in 'ipsecChannelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecChanAggTnlOutboundPackets.name: ipsecChanAggTnlOutboundPackets
ipsecChanAggTnlOutboundPackets.description: The total number of packets sent by all tunnels created by all channels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecChannelTunnelOutboundPackets' from the 'ipsecChannelEntry' of each channel in 'ipsecChannelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecChanAggTnlReceiveErrors.name: ipsecChanAggTnlReceiveErrors
ipsecChanAggTnlReceiveErrors.description: The total number of receive errors incurred in all tunnels created by all channels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecChannelTunnelReceiveErrors' from the 'ipsecChannelEntry' of each channel in 'ipsecChannelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecChanAggTnlSendErrors.name: ipsecChanAggTnlSendErrors
ipsecChanAggTnlSendErrors.description: The total number of send errors incurred in all tunnels created by all channels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecChannelTunnelSendErrors' from the 'ipsecChannelEntry' of each channel in 'ipsecChannelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecTunnelTable.name: ipsecTunnelTable
ipsecTunnelTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on IPsec SA suite-based tunnels. The number of rows is, at a minimum, the same as the number of IPsec SA suites in the entity that have identical selectors. Additional rows for tunnels without active IPsec SA suites may also appear in the table. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

ipsecTunnelEntry.name: ipsecTunnelEntry
ipsecTunnelEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular tunnel. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

ipsecTunnelType.name: ipsecTunnelType
ipsecTunnelType.description: The type of tunnel represented by this row. This is an implementation dependent value, used to assist in controlling how tunnels are sorted.

ipsecTunnelId.name: ipsecTunnelId
ipsecTunnelId.description: The index value of the selector table row that contains the selectors that are the identity of this tunnel. Specifically, this is the value of 'selectorIndex' from the appropriate row ('selectorEntry') from the table 'selectorTable' from the MIB 'ipsecMonModule'. (NOTE: Should this be an OBJECT IDENTIFIER instead?)

ipsecTunnelLocalIpAddrType.name: ipsecTunnelLocalIpAddrType
ipsecTunnelLocalIpAddrType.description: The type of address used by the local endpoint of the tunnel.

ipsecTunnelLocalIpAddress.name: ipsecTunnelLocalIpAddress
ipsecTunnelLocalIpAddress.description: The address used by the local endpoint of the tunnel.

ipsecTunnelRemoteIpAddrType.name: ipsecTunnelRemoteIpAddrType
ipsecTunnelRemoteIpAddrType.description: The type of address used by the remote endpoint of the tunnel.

ipsecTunnelRemoteIpAddress.name: ipsecTunnelRemoteIpAddress
ipsecTunnelRemoteIpAddress.description: The address used by the remote endpoint of the tunnel.

ipsecTunnelLocalEndpoint.name: ipsecTunnelLocalEndpoint
ipsecTunnelLocalEndpoint.description: The index of the local endpoint that negotiated this tunnel. It is the value of 'endpointIndex' from the correct row ('IkeEndpointEntry') of the 'ikeEndpointTable' from 'ikeMonModule'. (NOTE: Should this be an OBJECT IDENTIFIER instead?)

ipsecTunnelRemoteEndpoint.name: ipsecTunnelRemoteEndpoint
ipsecTunnelRemoteEndpoint.description: The index of the remote endpoint that negotiated this tunnel. It is the value of 'endpointIndex' from the correct row ('IkeEndpointEntry') of the 'ikeEndpointTable' from 'ikeMonModule'.

ipsecTunnelCurrentSaSuites.name: ipsecTunnelCurrentSaSuites
ipsecTunnelCurrentSaSuites.description: The number of phase 2 SA suites that are currently active that make up this tunnel. This value may be 0 if the tunnel has not yet been set up, or the implementation does not require the existence of phase 2 SA suites for the tunnel to exist, or if the tunnel is considered a permanent entry in the table by the implementation. This value should not include phase 2 SA suite establishment attempts in progress.

ipsecTunnelTotalSaSuites.name: ipsecTunnelTotalSaSuites
ipsecTunnelTotalSaSuites.description: The total number of phase 2 SA suites that are part of this tunnel that have been created in the entity since boot time. This value should not include failed phase 2 SA suite establishment attempts.

ipsecTunnelDeletedSaSuites.name: ipsecTunnelDeletedSaSuites
ipsecTunnelDeletedSaSuites.description: The total number of phase 2 SA suites that are part of this channel that have been deleted in the entity since boot time. The sum of 'ipsecTunnelCurrentSaSuites' and this value should equal 'ipsecTunnelTotalSaSuites'.

ipsecTunnelTimeUpSeconds.name: ipsecTunnelTimeUpSeconds
ipsecTunnelTimeUpSeconds.description: The total number of seconds since there has been at least one valid phase 2 SA suite supporting the channel. In other words, the number of seconds since the value of 'ipsecTunnelCurrentSaSuites' changed from 0 to any other value.

ipsecTunnelTimeDownSeconds.name: ipsecTunnelTimeDownSeconds
ipsecTunnelTimeDownSeconds.description: The total number of seconds since the last valid phase 2 SA suite supporting the channel was deleted. In other words, the number of seconds since the value of 'ipsecTunnelCurrentSaSuites' changed to 0 from any other value.

ipsecTunnelTotalInboundOctets.name: ipsecTunnelTotalInboundOctets
ipsecTunnelTotalInboundOctets.description: The total amount of traffic measured in bytes received by the tunnel. This is the sum of 'suiteInUserOctets' from the 'suiteEntry' of each phase 2 SA suite in 'suiteTable' that is part of this tunnel.

ipsecTunnelTotalOutboundOctets.name: ipsecTunnelTotalOutboundOctets
ipsecTunnelTotalOutboundOctets.description: The total amount of traffic measured in bytes sent by the tunnel. This is the sum of 'suiteOutUserOctets' from the 'suiteEntry' of each phase 2 SA suite in 'suiteTable' that is part of this tunnel.

ipsecTunnelTotalInboundPackets.name: ipsecTunnelTotalInboundPackets
ipsecTunnelTotalInboundPackets.description: The total number of packets received by the tunnel. This is the sum of 'suiteInPackets' from the 'suiteEntry' of each phase 2 SA suite in 'suiteTable' that is part of this tunnel.

ipsecTunnelTotalOutboundPackets.name: ipsecTunnelTotalOutboundPackets
ipsecTunnelTotalOutboundPackets.description: The total number of packets sent by the tunnel. This is the sum of 'suiteOutPackets' from the 'suiteEntry' of each phase 2 SA suite in 'suiteTable' that is part of this tunnel.

ipsecTunnelSendErrors.name: ipsecTunnelSendErrors
ipsecTunnelSendErrors.description: The total number of send errors in the tunnel. This is the sum of 'suiteSendErrors' from the 'suiteEntry' of each phase 2 SA suite in 'suiteTable' that is part of this tunnel.

ipsecTunnelReceiveErrors.name: ipsecTunnelReceiveErrors
ipsecTunnelReceiveErrors.description: The total number of receive errors in the tunnel. This is the sum of 'suiteReceiveErrors' from the 'suiteEntry' of each phase 2 SA suite in 'suiteTable' that is part of this tunnel.

ipsecTunnelSuiteTable.name: ipsecTunnelSuiteTable
ipsecTunnelSuiteTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on IPsec SA suites. The number of rows is the same as the number of IPsec SA suites in the entity. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

ipsecTunnelSuiteEntry.name: ipsecTunnelSuiteEntry
ipsecTunnelSuiteEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the identifiers to a particular SA suite. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

ipsecTunnelSuiteIndex.name: ipsecTunnelSuiteIndex
ipsecTunnelSuiteIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each SA suite in the tunnel. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1.

ipsecTunnelSuiteReference.name: ipsecTunnelSuiteReference
ipsecTunnelSuiteReference.description: The object identifier of the IPsec SA suite row that represents the IPsec SA suite in the tunnel. Specifically, the value of this object is the object identifier of 'suiteIndex' of the appropriate row ('SuiteEntry') in 'suiteTable' from 'ikeMonModule'.

ipsecTunAggTable.name: ipsecTunAggTable
ipsecTunAggTable.description: The optional (conceptual) table containing information on aggregate statistics for the tunnel types. The number of rows is the same as the number of tunnel types supported by the entity. The maximum number of rows is implementation dependent.

ipsecTunAggEntry.name: ipsecTunAggEntry
ipsecTunAggEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the aggregate statistics for a specific tunnel type. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

ipsecTunAggCurrentTunnels.name: ipsecTunAggCurrentTunnels
ipsecTunAggCurrentTunnels.description: The number of tunnels that are currently active that are of the specified type. This value should not include tunnel establishment attempts in progress.

ipsecTunAggTotalTunnels.name: ipsecTunAggTotalTunnels
ipsecTunAggTotalTunnels.description: The total number of tunnels of this type that have been created in the entity since boot time. This value should not include failed tunnel establishment attempts.

ipsecTunAggDeletedTunnels.name: ipsecTunAggDeletedTunnels
ipsecTunAggDeletedTunnels.description: The total number of tunnels of this type that have been deleted in the entity since boot time. The sum of 'ipsecTunAggCurrentTunnels' and this value should equal 'ipsecTunAggTotalTunnels'.

ipsecTunAggInboundOctets.name: ipsecTunAggInboundOctets
ipsecTunAggInboundOctets.description: The total amount of traffic measured in bytes received by all tunnels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecTunnelInboundOctets' from the 'ipsecTunnelEntry' of each tunnel in 'ipsecTunnelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecTunAggOutboundOctets.name: ipsecTunAggOutboundOctets
ipsecTunAggOutboundOctets.description: The total amount of traffic measured in bytes sent by all tunnels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecTunnelOutboundOctets' from the 'ipsecTunnelEntry' of each tunnel in 'ipsecTunnelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecTunAggInboundPackets.name: ipsecTunAggInboundPackets
ipsecTunAggInboundPackets.description: The total number of packets received by all tunnels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecTunnelInboundPackets' from the 'ipsecTunnelEntry' of each tunnel in 'ipsecTunnelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecTunAggOutboundPackets.name: ipsecTunAggOutboundPackets
ipsecTunAggOutboundPackets.description: The total number of packets sent by all tunnels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecTunnelOutboundPackets' from the 'ipsecTunnelEntry' of each tunnel in 'ipsecTunnelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecTunAggSendErrors.name: ipsecTunAggSendErrors
ipsecTunAggSendErrors.description: The total number of send errors incurred by all tunnels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecTunnelSendErrors' from the 'ipsecTunnelEntry' of each tunnel in 'ipsecTunnelTable' that is of this type.

ipsecTunAggReceiveErrors.name: ipsecTunAggReceiveErrors
ipsecTunAggReceiveErrors.description: The total number of receive errors incurred by all tunnels of this type. This is the sum of 'ipsecTunnelReceiveErrors' from the 'ipsecTunnelEntry' of each tunnel in 'ipsecTunnelTable' that is of this type.

tunnelBySelectorsTable.name: tunnelBySelectorsTable
tunnelBySelectorsTable.description: The (conceptual) table that sorts the tunnels by the selectors. The number of rows in this table is the same as the number of tunnels in the entity.

tunnelBySelectorsEntry.name: tunnelBySelectorsEntry
tunnelBySelectorsEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) referencing a particular tunnel. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.
